{"id": "1448036903365378180", "channel_id": "1448036903365378180", "type": 0, "author_id": "579993591565385728", "author_name": "fantagan", "author_bot": false, "content": "What resources, if any, are refunded by the Special?", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T19:41:40.987000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1448036904091123782", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 549646, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1448036903365378180/1448036904091123782/image.png?ex=69cccc35&is=69cb7ab5&hm=b21d9a13c8c1f389a0a4a593136b03599862fabaa96769ccd980465a2e77a265&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1448036903365378180", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "What resources are refunded by the Special (the brown pyramid)", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747463379390545"]}
{"id": "1447918591348572241", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "804427303282278472", "author_name": "thespookboo", "author_bot": false, "content": "ok?\nthx for the recommendations but i still dont really understand how the caro thing even works like whats the basic idea", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T11:51:33.204000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447922616512811069", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Each realm (chaos, aequor, caro, ultra) has its own unique mechanics.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:07:32.878000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447922762474586303", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "For Caro, it's the furnace and embryo mechanic.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:08:07.678000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447923225483939901", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "First, i'll explain the embryo mechanic. Above the team/characters, you'll see a red bar.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:09:58.068000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:13:41.179000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447924787543408801", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "This bar can be filled up to 100% to generate 1 embryo or baby (term used by the playerbase).", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:16:10.492000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:22:42.299000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447926203976515726", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "The red bar can be filled in different ways:\n- At turn start, it's automatically filled up by 30% (gets higher the lower the team hp is) \n- Caro characters have command cards that have an effect of increasing the red bar by a certain percentage.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:21:48.196000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:22:52.311000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447927935079288842", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "The embryo/baby is mainly used for 2 reasons.\nFirst, it can be used on the characters directly to give them 30 aliemus and 10% temporary crit rate.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:28:40.923000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:52:57.694000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447928282799411263", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Second, it is used to trigger the Devour effect seen on the exalt of Caro characters.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:30:03.826000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447928956283256873", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "The Devour effect is an additional effect unique to the exalt of Caro characters. It can only be triggered by consuming an embryo/baby in hand when you activate the exalt/overexalt.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:32:44.397000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447930650891128852", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Then, I'll talk about the other mechanic, furnace.\nBesides the red bar, you'll see a red orb.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:39:28.423000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447933869172195478", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "This is also filled up in different ways:\n- At turn start, accumulate 3% of Max HP into the furnace. \n- After a battle, accumulate 5% of Max HP into the furnace. \n- For each leftover embryos/babies after a battle, accumulate 5% of Max HP into the furnace.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:52:15.721000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447934557784510554", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "The red orb can be consumed by clicking on it to recover HP equal to the filled amount.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:54:59.899000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T12:56:16.677000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447937212669755413", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Almost forget to mention this. \nWhen you trigger the Devour effect by exalting a Caro character, you gain 4% of Max HP as a Shield and 2% of Max HP as Temporary STR. This only activates once per turn on the first successful Devour effect trigger. The value goes up the lower the team HP is.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:05:32.873000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447937485597446186", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "That's explains the Caro realm mechanics.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:06:37.944000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447939319451877537", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "For Caro Awakeners/characters to look out for:\n- Helot: Catena/GHelot (DPS) \n- Thais (Support) \n- Doresain (DPS) \n- Pickman (Support) \n- Salvador (Shield, DPS)", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:13:55.169000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:14:15.299000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447941568882544740", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Thais is the Best Caro Support in the game at the moment. She can  generate aliemus and STR. She can provide vulnerable and weakness. She fills the red bar by a lot. She can duplicate command cards in hand with reduced cost. She is very good and provides a lot of utility as a support.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:22:51.475000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447943330037104800", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Helot: Catena/GHelot is a DPS carry specializing in bleed dmg. \nHer damage is top tier and she is very straightforward to play with.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:29:51.367000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447944733841428580", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "Salvador is mostly used for his shielding but can be a DPS carry if you have enlightens (dupes) on him. His kit is tied to the furnace mechanic.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:35:26.060000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
{"id": "1447946733278728275", "channel_id": "1447283410572677211", "type": 0, "author_id": "596922317142228992", "author_name": "juuki0811", "author_bot": false, "content": "If you want more info, look in the guides section. I think there are Caro-focused ones I read before.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:43:22.763000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "💯", "emoji_id": null, "count": 3}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447283410572677211", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "how do caro teams work?", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
